          "description": "Per-frame hold duration in milliseconds, indexed the same as frames. When provided it is authoritative for playback timing and fps is ignored while advancing frames (still accepted as a display-only average). Use this to preserve uneven hold-frames — e.g. an Aseprite export where one frame intentionally lingers longer than the rest."
