          "returnType": null,
          "description": "Per-frame local translation in local (pre-scale) pixels, indexed the same as frames, applied on top of the sprite's own position/origin. Use this to keep frames anchored to a stable point when a source atlas trims frames to different sizes (Aseprite's spriteSourceSize) — without it, differently-trimmed frames would jitter around their own top-left."
        },
